The paper deals with extending description logics (DLs) with non-monotonic reasoning features, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the semantics and syntax of defeasible subsumption, which is a topic in logic (cs.LO) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also presents an algorithm for the computation of rational closure of a defeasible ontology, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR) and DLs (cs.DL).
